rComments: This class was extremely interesting but the slides could get a bit confusing. You have to do a LOT of reading for the weekly quizzes but if you do the reading you have an A+. For the exams you need to do a lot of studying.

My least favourite teacher by far. Wanted to change the syllabus halfway through the semester and didn't trust her students enough, seemed like she was teaching a high-school. Quizzes were very easy and will be the solid ground of your final grade.

Did not enjoy taking a class with this professor. She was so boring in lectures and randomly decided halfway through the semester that she was changing our syllabus without consulting the class. I was not impressed at all.

She was really nice and sweet, but every time I thought I did good on a test, it turned out my grade was awful. Her readings were very long but interesting. You really need to study for the midterm and final exam.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Participation matters', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: literally the worst class to take as an elective. She takes the 9 hours of work per week seriously with long readings every week, quizzes, mandatory participation, etc. she makes slides without info and talks (which makes note taking hard). overall not a good class and hard to pass without doing excessive amounts of work
I love her!! i'm taking more classes with her

She's SUPER nice! If you attend her lecture and seriously listen to her? EASY A. Whenever she says it will be on the test, important hw for no points: MARK IT DOWN. Would recommend her 100%! She is passionate and helpful. Just take notes and listen to her. :))
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: She is super nice, but gosh her lectures are nothing like her exam. And she would blame the whole class when only a few people cheated on a quiz that counts for like 3% ... Be serious in her class (don't underestimate her class), take a lot of notes. READINGS are IMPORTANT. Whenever she gives you an exercise that does not count, it will be on exam.

This was my 2nd class with Prof. Portilla, and I signed up for a 3rd this summer! I liked how organized her style of teaching was, and how the grade was split between weekly quizzes and clearly graded assignments. She also dropped the 2 lowest quiz marks which was nice. She was very kind, and clearly knew the subject matter she was teaching.

She is an amazing professor! Shes really interesting to listen to during zoom lectures. She explains well the PowerPoint and its easy to tell she is passionate about her job. If I could grade her higher I would.

This prof is really nice don't get me wrong, but the class was not fun and I don't recommend taking it if you don't like to read. (there are readings and a quiz to do about them every week). She's also really monotone and kind of boring to listen to. Her PowerPoints are really unclear and she goes on about subjects that aren't even on the slides.

Honestly I don't understand why she has such a bad grade... I don't know if it's because this class was online for me but I thought she was great! Clearly passionate about her subject! I think I would take her again. The only down side is that there's LOTS of readings so GET READY TO READ !!
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Definitely not as bad as the reviews display her. (Fall 2019) I found her to be very caring and if you actually do the readings and pay attention, you can learn a lot. I found that the lectures make up for some unclear topics explained in class. She quizzes the students based on every week's lecture, but is really not severe, easy A on the quizzes.

She has no sense of responsibility. Since my first language is not French, I had difficulties understanding the purely academic readings. I wrote her an email asking for her clarification for some concepts but she never replied. If you don't care about your students or just have no time answering an email , do NOT come to uottawa to be a professor!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: She's nice and she cares about the success of her students. She does go on random topics sometimes but her class is still clear. She is a pretty fair marker and you can get about 35% of your grade just by doing the readings and showing up for the quizzes. Only downside is that the questions in her exams are weirdly put which might confuse people.
she talks alot, pass like 30 minutes on one slide and the rest she pass them really fast because shes running out of time so... nobody understands. boring class and actually tough grader.

final exam was only 3 questions that basically just covered the last course and 10 multiple choices on the readings. it was surprising to see such an awful exam that did not cover the course material properly i was disappointed. she isnt clear in what she wants from students. going to class is useless. she comes to class late & rushes ppts at end
J'ai vraiment aimé le prof. Super interessante et maitrise bien la matiere!

I've taken this prof before and must say she has improved. She's caring about her students and makes sure that everyone understands. Her lectures are interesting, even if she does go off topic at times. She also gives many heavy readings and a few papers. We had many videos, a guest speaker and group discussions in this class.

rComments: She never replied to my email even though I asked her something very urgent. Quiz in group every lecture which means you have to be present and do the readings.
Très plate
She talks a lot and basically says the same thing all time. Her assistants are as useless as her. I dont recommand this course.
She is a very nice person but a horrible teacher. She talks for hours about nothing and still expects the students to understand and remember everything. Her slides a very vague and useless.
Prof takes a lot of class time to talk about subjects that are not important for this class. Will rush through her powepoints and won't start back were she left off the class before.
Not specific on anything and pass 2 hours on the same slide, so pass the other slides super quickly because she's running out of time
Talks a lot but doesn't really say much... BORING

She was consistently late for class, and would then blame the class for not getting through all the material. She's boring to listen to and often unorganized. Tests were fine but she would often say one important thing halfway through class, making it necessary to sit through her lectures.
She's really nice but BORING
its something else!!
She's boring.

Quiz à chaque cours du vendredi matin, et elle le donne seulement au dernier 20 minutes du cours faire sur qu'on reste toute le long, elle parle comme si on devait tout comprendre quand on comprend rien du vocabulaire qu'elle utilise, tu fini par perdre l'intérêt pendant le cours, à ne pas recommander!! Erreur d'avoir pris ce cours.

Very nice and approachable. She was often times late to the class and she does these quizzes that are fairly simple but sometimes she'll randomly do "group" quizzes. So you have to partner up the day of the quiz. She allows only 15mins for a quiz which really isn't enough time to write 1page with a partner who may or may not have read the material

Professor Portilla tries hard to make lectures less boring, but she often trails off and goes on long tangents which are hard to follow. Any information you need for the midterm is on her powerpoints and in the readings (usually just the ppts). Usually doesn't have a final, includes lots of papers which are easy to ace.

She was only late like 2 or 3 times... In general she's a great prof who expects you to work for the grade. Her exams are not hard if you pay attention in class, there is a lot of readings but their actually relevant. You get 10% just for participation (being in class and doing the quizzes). I recommend her classes! Same for FEM2511!

Content is incredibly beginner for people in Social Sc.  1st year sociology basic concepts, then expects intellectual stimulation by low level academic lectures, research & writing. You will loose all your points for any critical theory application and interdisciplinary thought. You must regurgitate everything she teaches in your work.

Enseignante toujours prete pour aider ses eleves.  Evidemment elle sattend a ce que vous travailler.  Ca fais 3 fois que je la prend et jai adorer!! TOp 5 prof que jai durant mon cheminement.  Par contre attendez-vous a faire vos lectures.
She likes getting the class involved during lectures. Easy exams if you study. Assigns many readings. Assigns in-class exercises. She is always available and very understanding.

She is a very lovely person, although she was rarely on time for class and often arrived 15-20 minutes late. She graded very severely and was very vague with feedback/ways to improve. Attendance/participation points were taken. Her use of technology was very useful however, made it easier to stay focused during long 3 hour lectures.
